@Deprecated
public <T extends org.eclipse.jdt.core.IJavaElement> void update(IAnnotation<T> annotation,
                                                                            java.util.Set<IParamValuePair> paramValuePairs,
                                                                            boolean replacePreviousPairs)
            throws AnnotationGeneratorException,
                   org.eclipse.core.runtime.CoreException
Deprecated. - use public void update(final IAnnotation annotation) instead.

Updates the Param-Value Pairs of specific Annotation.

Parameters:
annotation - - Annotation, which will be updated.
paramValuePairs - which will be updated. Old pairs will be replaced with the new once.
replacePreviousPairs - boolean value which specifies the way, how new IParamValuePairs will be updated. If the value is true, the Set with the old IParamValuePairs will be cleared and the new values will be applied. If the value is false the old pairs will be kept and will be updated with the values from the new Set, if there are params which do not exist in the old one, they will be added.
Throws:
org.eclipse.core.runtime.CoreException
AnnotationGeneratorException
